shared_text:
Lewis and Clark Jr High Patriots Athletics
September 9 at 8:53 AM ¬∑

Please share this page. This will have all updated information regarding athletics at Lewis and Clark Junior High.

Due to COVID-19 our athletics has been changed for this year. As of now we are planning on starting athletics in January.

The planned schedule for each sports is as follows:

Boys Basketball can begin practice January 4th and season will run until the week of February 22nd

Volleyball practice can begin practice January 11th and season will run until the week of March 1st

Track and Field practice can begin March 1 and season will run through Mid-May

Girls basketball can begin practice March 8th and season will run until the week of April 26th.

Please make sure you get your physicals updated before any season starts.

If you have any questions you can email the AD at sflowers@wrh15.org

shared_text:
Hartford Elementary
August 7 at 2:28 PM ¬∑

Just a little update.
Please remember things are changing daily here for us at Hartford Elementary. We are having in class school this year, Mon. - Fri. with the day being shortened to DISMISSAL TIME AT 1:30.
FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL IS AUG. 19th.
The 19th, 20th and 21st are half days with DISMISSAL AT 11:30.
MASK ARE A MUST! (We will supply ONE mask to every student).
Temperatures will be taken at the door and before students get on the bus. As the students enter the building they will go straight to their classroom.
MEET THE TEACHER; KG will have meet the teacher night by appointments. Grades 1-5 will be a video meet the teacher night. Teachers will be in contact with more information.
We are following all CDC guidelines and doing everything possible to keep our students and staff safe and healthy!

post_text:
Dear Parents,

Governor Pritzker has just informed school superintendents across Illinois that in reaction to the COVID-19, or coronavirus, spread in our state, he is issuing a mandated closure of all K-12 schools starting Tuesday, March 17th and lasting through Monday, March 30th. As of right now, all Wood River-Hartford schools will be open for student attendance on Monday, March 16th, and will begin the mandated closure as of Tuesday, March 17th.
Please develop plans now for your children and their childcare during this closure, and prepare for the possibility that this closure may be extended if this situation continues to evolve. During the mandated closure, all district events and activities will be cancelled as well. The district webpage, Facebook pages, email, and SchoolMessenger phone calls will be our primary sources for updating parents on this continuously evolving situation.

Please develop plans now for your children and their childcare during this closure, and prepare for the possibility that this closure may be extended if this situation continues to evolve. During the mandated closure, all district events and activities will be cancelled as well.
